Steps:
1. Create a blank image using dd
dd if=/dev/zero of=blank.img bs=4M count=50

2. Mount that blank img on a loop device
sudo losetup loop0 blank.img

3. Partition the loop0 mounted img
sudo fdisk /dev/loop0
o <- clear partitions
n <- new
p <- primary
1 <- 1st drive partition
ENTER <- first sector
ENTER <- second sector
t <- type
c <- W95 FAT32 (LBA)
w <- write and exit

4. Format the partition on loop0
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/loop0p1

5. Mount the partition
mkdir mnt
sudo mount /dev/loop0p1 mnt

6. Copy the kernel and stuff
sudo cp <path of stuff> mnt/

7. Unmount partition
sudo umount mnt

8. Detach loop device
sudo losetup -d /dev/loop0

9. Rename blank to something useful
mv blank.img custom.img


custom.img should be written to an sdcard
